The paper presents a formal embedding of input/output logic in classical higher-order logic, which is a topic that falls under the area of logic and automated reasoning (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of off-the-shelf higher-order theorem provers and proof assistants, which are tools commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also touches on the automation of reasoning tasks, which is a topic in software engineering (cs.SE) and machine learning (cs.LG).
